<h1>E-Learning Platform - Rails MVC</h1>

<h2>Run</h2>
<pre>
rails new elearning_platform
cd elearning_platform
bundle add bcrypt
rails generate model User name:string email:string password_digest:string
rails generate model Course title:string description:text user:references
rails generate model Lesson title:string content:text course:references
rails generate model Enrollment user:references course:references
rails generate controller Sessions new create destroy
rails generate scaffold Courses title:string description:text user:references
rails generate scaffold Lessons title:string content:text course:references
rails db:create db:migrate
rails server
</pre>

<h2>Models</h2>
<pre>
class User &lt; ApplicationRecord
  has_secure_password
  has_many :courses, dependent: :destroy
  has_many :enrollments, dependent: :destroy
  has_many :enrolled_courses, through: :enrollments, source: :course
  validates :name, :email, presence: true
end

class Course &lt; ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :user
  has_many :lessons, dependent: :destroy
  has_many :enrollments, dependent: :destroy
  has_many :users, through: :enrollments
end

class Lesson &lt; ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :course
end

class Enrollment &lt; ApplicationRecord
  belongs_to :user
  belongs_to :course
  validates :user_id, uniqueness: { scope: :course_id }
end
</pre>

<p>Create login and signup forms, then use scaffold CRUD for courses and lessons.</p>


# Elearning Platform (Rails)

Brief steps to create and run this app using the terminal, plus what you need
to change for your own setup.

## 1) Create the app
```powershell
rails new elearning_platform
cd elearning_platform
```

## 2) Generate models
```powershell
rails g model User name:string email:string password_digest:string
rails g model Course title:string description:text user:references
rails g model Lesson title:string content:text course:references
rails g model Enrollment user:references course:references
```

## 3) Add associations and validations
Edit these files:
- app/models/user.rb
- app/models/course.rb
- app/models/lesson.rb
- app/models/enrollment.rb

Change each file to include:
```ruby
# app/models/user.rb
has_secure_password
has_many :courses, dependent: :destroy
has_many :enrollments, dependent: :destroy
has_many :enrolled_courses, through: :enrollments, source: :course
validates :name, :email, presence: true

# app/models/course.rb
belongs_to :user
has_many :lessons, dependent: :destroy
has_many :enrollments, dependent: :destroy
has_many :users, through: :enrollments

# app/models/lesson.rb
belongs_to :course

# app/models/enrollment.rb
belongs_to :user
belongs_to :course
validates :user_id, uniqueness: { scope: :course_id }
```

## 4) Create controllers + views
```powershell
rails g controller Users
rails g controller Courses
rails g controller Lessons
rails g controller Enrollments
```

Then add CRUD actions and views (index, show, new, edit) for each resource.
If you want a quick starting point, scaffold is faster:
```powershell
rails g scaffold User name:string email:string password_digest:string
rails g scaffold Course title:string description:text user:references
rails g scaffold Lesson title:string content:text course:references
rails g scaffold Enrollment user:references course:references
```

## 5) Update routes
Edit `config/routes.rb` and change to:
```ruby
root "sessions#new"
resources :users
resources :courses
resources :lessons
resources :enrollments
```

## 6) Migrate and run
```powershell
rails db:migrate
rails server
```

Visit:
- http://127.0.0.1:3000/users
- http://127.0.0.1:3000/courses
- http://127.0.0.1:3000/lessons
- http://127.0.0.1:3000/enrollments

## What to change for your own project
- Change model fields in `rails g model ...` commands to match your data.
- Update validations and relations in `app/models/*.rb`.
- Replace the example controllers/views with your app’s real UI.
- Update `config/routes.rb` to only include resources you actually need.
